Here are both approaches for navigating from `ProductListPage` to `ProductDetailsPage`:

## 1. Route Registration (AppShell.xaml.cs)

```csharp
public partial class AppShell : Shell
{
    public AppShell()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
    }
}
```

## 2. Navigating from ProductListPage

```csharp
// Approach A: Pass product ID as a query string
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?id={product.Id}");
}

// Approach B: Pass the full Product object
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
}
```

## 3. Receiving Data via IQueryAttributable on the ViewModel

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: receive the string ID
        if (query.TryGetValue("id", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID
        }

        // Approach B: receive the full object
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
            ProductId = product.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- Query string (`?id=...`) passes strings only â€” use for simple values.
- `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` passes objects by reference â€” use for complex types.
- `ApplyQueryAttributes` is called automatically when the page is navigated to; the ViewModel must implement `IQueryAttributable`.
- Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions.
